  "title": "La Rochefoucauld §laroch_494: What makes us see that men know their faults better than we imagine, is that ...",
  "body": "What makes us see that men know their faults better than we imagine, is that they are never wrong when they speak of their conduct; the same self-love that usually blinds them enlightens them, and gives them such true views as to make them suppress or disguise the smallest thing that might be censured.",
